    <td bgcolor="#FFFF00" width="100%"><strong>IMPORTANT NOTE:</strong><p><br>
    Page 30 of the LSRS Manual indicates that a Subsurface Salinity deduction should only be
    made if it is greater than the Surface Salinity deduction. This has not been implemented.
    It was decided that Salinity is a minor factor in Organic soils and that Reaction would
    most often be the major factor.</p>
    <p>&nbsp;</p></td>
