<p>&nbsp;</p>

<table border="1" width="100%">
  <tbody><tr>
    <td bgcolor="#FFFF00" width="100%"><strong>IMPORTANT NOTE:</strong><p><br>
    Only the larger of the two <strong>Subsurface</strong> deductions for Reaction and
    Salinity is used for soil rating calculations purposes.</p>
    <p>Thus if the <strong>Subsurface Reaction</strong> deduction is 15 and
    the <strong>Subsurface Salinity</strong> deduction is 7, only the 15 is used for further
    rating calculations (this is similar to Surface rules).</p>
    <p>&nbsp;</p></td>
  </tr>
</tbody></table>

